
                        TMTEST README


tmtest makes functional tests as easy to write as shell scripts.


INSTALL

	make install

	Now tmtest is installed in your home directory, ~/bin, and ready
	to be used.  Use "prefix" to put the executable elsewhere:

	make install prefix=/usr/local


USE

	tmtest            (runs all tests in the current dir and all subdirs)


LICENSE

	LGPL.  See COPYING for more.

